Irene Mwangi reports for Capital FM that the official campaign period has commenced with the Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission (IEBC) clearing presidential aspirants ahead of the elections. Despite jitters that Wiper Party leader Kalonzo Musyoka has been locked out of the race, he is scheduled to appear on June 4, 2022 for the clearance exercise. On the same day, United Democratic Alliance presidential candidate William Ruto is set to appear. Azimio Coalition Presidential flag bearer Raila Odinga will appear for the clearance exercise on June 5, 2022. The IEBC Chairperson Wafula Chebukati is the returning officer for the exercise where 16 candidates have been shortlisted. Candidates will need to verify their identity details to confirm their Kenyan citizenship. They will also need a Sh200,000 nomination fee, have at least a bacherlor's degree and 2,000 endorsing signatures from at least 24 counties.